    <h2><abbr>MPL</abbr> Programming Language</h2>
    <a href="https://github.com/yugyfoog/MPL">github.com/yugyfoog/MPL</a>
    <p>
      <abbr>MPL</abbr> is a mathematical programming language that I designed.
      It is a simple scripting language.
      It can be used interactivly but that was not my intension,
      so don't expect it to be user friendly.

      I wanted a small/simple language that can be used for calculations
      that are too cumbersome for a hand-held calculator, yet dosen't require
      a real programming language.

      I also don't like how many mathematical programming languages
      conflate arrays and vectors/matricies. I wanted a language
      that had array semantics so multipling two arrays produces
      an array of products. However, for multipling two vectors I want a
      dot product and multipling a <em>n</em>x<em>m</em> matrix with a
      <em>m</em>x<em>p</em> matrix should result in a
      <em>n</em>x<em>p</em> matrix.
    </p>
    <p>
      This interpreter is mostly finished for the core language.
      I still need more work on error checking and reporting.
      There is still a lot of work to do for the standard library.
    </p>

