    <h1>Why yugyfoog?</h1>
    <p>
      Many years ago I needed a watch.
      While looking at watches in a store I saw some Mickey Mouse watches.
      I remembered how when I was a kid a wanted one.
      There were other Disney watches there too and I noticed that a goofy watch was backwards.
      Something about a watch whose hands moved counter clockwise appealed to me.
      There's no reason a clock's hands move clockwise other than convention. So why not?
      I didn't buy the watch then but must have told someone about it because next Christmas
      I had one.
      After that every birthday and Christmas I receved more and more Goofy presents.
      I became the <q>Goofy Guy</q> of the family.
    </p>
    <p>
      Years later, but still awhile ago, I was signing up for some sort of instant messaging service.
      I didn't want to use my real name (boring) but I have no nickname.
      So I first choose <q>goofyguy</q>. But that was taken. Then I though spelling "goofyguy" backwards (like the watch)
      would be a goofy thing to do. The rest is history.
    </p>
